Nomura Asset Management Malaysia Sdn. Bhd.Nomura Islamic Asset Management Sdn. Bhd.











Nomura Asset Management Malaysia Sdn. Bhd. (NAM Malaysia) was incorporated in September 2006, joining the ranks of other top international asset managers' presence in Malaysia, as part of the special scheme for foreign fund management companies introduced by the Securities Commission Malaysia in 2005 to strengthen the Malaysian capital market.
In order to leverage on Malaysia's leadership role in Islamic finance and fund management, we established Nomura Islamic Asset Management Sdn. Bhd. (NIAM) in November 2008 with the ambition to build ourselves as the global Islamic hub for the Nomura Asset Management (NAM) Group.
NAM Malaysia (Company Registration No.: 748695-A) and NIAM (Company Registration No.: 838564-T) are registered as limited companies under the Companies Act (Malaysia) 1965. The offices are licensed under the Capital Markets and Services Act 2007 (CMSA) for the regulated activity of fund management since December 2006 (NAM Malaysia) and January 2009 (NIAM).  Both NAM Malaysia and NIAM are 100% owned by Nomura Asset Management Singapore Limited (NAMS).



Our investment approach is based on the understanding that markets are not fully efficient and that active management through fundamental research can add value. We consider the best investment approach to be combining both bottom-up and top-down strategies, with a bias towards stock selection, and portfolio risk control techniques should be at the heart of the investment management process. With a team based investment management style, the investment process is structured to rely heavily on the insight we gain from our locally based investment team to add value to our clients' assets.
Over the years, our investment philosophy and disciplined investment process have delivered consistent long-term investment results for our clients.



The establishment of the Malaysian offices aims to strengthen our relationship with our existing and targeted clients in the region. With a variety of clients globally, encompassing pension funds, government agencies and institutional investors, together with our depths of resource worldwide, we are confident that we can tailor our service to suit all our clients' investment requirements. This comprises of global and regional offerings to our clients in the region including the Middle East.
We have an established reputation in Malaysia and are part of the core Asia Pacific ex Japan team responsible for the management of non-Japan Pacific Basin regional equity portfolios as well as marketing and client relationships within the region.  Our capabilities have also expanded over the years to include on the ground investment capabilities in global Islamic equities, global Sukuk and Islamic fixed income securities.
As the global Islamic hub of NAM Group, we have successfully built ourselves as one of the top 20 Islamic fund management companies in the world, based on assets under management (Asian Investor, March 2014) within a short span of time.



